Use the standard library
This is how to median of l:
   Remember that a is []
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this l's length times:
      Add a to item i in l
      Increase i
   End do

   Remember that n is a's length
   Remember that pass is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that j is 0
      Do this (diff of n and 1) times:
         When item j in a is more than item (sum of j and 1) in a, then:
            Remember that temp is item j in a
            Remember that item j in a is item (sum of j and 1) in a
            Remember that item (sum of j and 1) in a is temp
         End when
         Increase j
      End do
      Increase pass
   End do

   Remember that r is remainder of n and 2
   When r is 1, then:
      The answer is item (quotient of n and 2) in a
   But, if not:
      Remember that right is quotient of n and 2
      Remember that left is diff of right and 1
      The answer is quotient of (sum of (tofloat of item left in a) and (tofloat of item right in a)) and 2
   End when
Now you know